        <updateDate>2019-05-20T20:36:44Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations Readiness Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Defense (DOD) to develop and implement a capability to conduct joint campaign modeling for joint electromagnetic spectrum operations. The term &quot;joint electromagnetic spectrum operations&quot; means those activities consisting of electronic warfare and joint electromagnetic spectrum management operations used to exploit, attack, protect, and manage the electromagnetic operational environment to achieve a military commander's objectives.</p> <p> DOD shall: (1) conduct an assessment of required joint electromagnetic spectrum operations capabilities and capacity based on a review of all level 3 and level 4 contingency plans, and (2) submit to the congressional defense committees reports on its readiness with respect to joint electromagnetic spectrum operations.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
